******
[2] BioBio
Date: Fri 2 Mar 2012
Source BioBio Chile [in Spanish, trans. Mod. TY, edited]
http://www.biobiochile.cl/2012/03/02/autoridades-sanitarias-confirman-ocho-casos-de-contagio-por-virus-hanta-en-la-region-del-bio-bio.shtml


A new victim of [a] hantavirus [infection] died in the BioBio region. A young man of 21 years died in Santiago after becoming infected in the Los Alamos community, Arauco province. The health authority confirmed [the etiology] of this cases and said that the total cases in the region is 8. Of these 8 infected individuals, 5 have died.

[This last case] traveled to the Sara de Lebu area in the Los Alamos community to visit his mother in mid-January [2012]. After various days in this place, and travel in a native forest at night, the young man became infected with the virus. He arrived in Santiago on 22 Feb [2012] and developed the 1st symptoms and was taken rapidly to the Davila clinic, where he remained hospitalized in serious condition. Although under intensive therapy, he died this past Thursday [1 Mar 2012].

Finally, the Health SEREMI [regional governmental ministerial unit] , Boris Oportus, stated that this is the 8th case in the area, and of 8 other suspected cases, 5 were discarded and another 3 await confirmation.

[Published by Alvaro Aguero; information from Valeska Vivallo]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
